Title: An Act to Protect Children's Identification by Requiring Public
Official Title: An Act to Protect Children's Identification by Requiring Public
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1002
H.P. 649 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
Schools to Use the Name and Gender Specified on a Child's Birth
Certificate
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative LYMAN of Livermore Falls.
Cosponsored by Senator TIMBERLAKE of Androscoggin and
Representatives: DAIGLE of Fort Kent, DRINKWATER of Milford, EDER of Waterboro,
FREDERICKS of Sanford, GRIFFIN of Levant, HAGGAN of Hampden, SOBOLESKI of
Phillips, Senator: LIBBY of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §14 is enacted to read:
3 §14. Student identification
4 Notwithstanding Title 5, chapter 337, personnel of a public school and public charter
5 school authorized under chapter 112 shall refer to a minor student by the name and gender
6 listed on the student's official record of birth submitted to the school at the time of
7 enrollment pursuant to section 6002 unless the minor student's parent provides written
8 permission stating otherwise or documentation of a legal change of name or gender is
9 provided to the school.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill provides that public school and public charter school personnel must refer to
1122 a minor student by the name and gender listed on the student's official record of birth
1133 submitted to the school at the time of enrollment unless the minor student's parent or
1144 guardian provides written permission stating otherwise or documentation of a legal change
1155 of name or gender is provided to the school.
Page 1 - 132LR1511(01)
